    <h1><span class="hash">#</span>about</h1>

    <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7;">
      I'm <strong>Karthikeyan Natarajan Gnanapalam</strong> — Karthik for short. I've been building software since 2008 and shipping it on the internet ever since. Born in <em>Madurai</em>, raised on bazaar logic and engineering textbooks, currently splitting time between <em>Bengaluru and Dubai</em>.
    </p>

    <p>I optimize for <strong>structural advantage</strong>, <strong>autonomy</strong>, and <strong>compounding technological leverage</strong>. I think in mechanisms, not narratives. The systems that win are usually the boring ones.</p>

    <p>These days I'm a <strong>full-time trader on perpetual futures markets</strong> — running my own quantitative models in public at <a href="https://feaws.xyz" target="_blank" rel="noopener">feaws.xyz</a>. The trading is the proof. The writing is the residue.</p>

